The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Tuesday, August 17, 2004 Digest AUGUST 15 DIGEST 
 Michael Schumacher after winning the Hungarian Grand Prix in Budapest on Sunday. (Reuters) A record dozen for Schumi Budapest: Michael Schumacher won Sundays Hungarian Grand Prix to become the first driver to claim 12 races in a single season. He has only failed once all season (Monaco). Schumachers victory, with teammate Rubens Barrichello coming second, also brought Ferrari their sixth straight constructors championship with five races remaining. All but mathematically clinched, Schumacher could wrap up an unprecedented seventh drivers title in two weeks at the Belgian GP. STANDINGS
Top-5 drivers1. Michael Schumacher (Ger, 120 pts); 2. Rubens Barrichello (Bra, 82); 3. Jenson Button (GBR, 65); 4. Jarno Trulli (Ita, 46) 5. Fernando Alonso (Spa, 45). Top-5 constructors 1. Ferrari (202 pts); 2. Renault (91); 3. BAR (83); 4. Williams (54); 5. McLaren (37).Pakistan A win Nairobi: Pakistan A captain Misbah-ul Haq steered his team to a three-wicket win over Kenya in the fifth one-day match of the Nairobi tri-series Sunday. The right-hander, who scored an unbeaten 64, shared a 113-run stand for the seventh wicket with Man-of-the-Match Riaz Afridi (66 off 62 balls) that helped turn the game in their favour after an early slump. Kenya, who had made 215 after being sent in, looked to be heading for victory when pacer Thomas Odoyo took three quick wickets. Its JSCA now Jamshedpur: The Bihar Cricket Association (BCA), in a resolution on Sunday, decided to change the name of the 69-year-old body to Jharkhand State Cricket Association (JSCA). This was made known by a senior official after the BCA general body meeting on Sunday.Sanias double Hyderabad: Sania Mirza won a double crown at the $10,000 ITF womens meet in Hampstead. According to information received here, the Indian girl downed Aussie Jaslin Hewitt 4-6, 6-1, 6-1 to win her second successive singles title following her triumph in Wrexham last week. It was the tenth career singles title for the 17-year old. In the doubles final, Sania and Rushmi Chakravarthy trounced Anna Hawkins (Britain) and Nicole Renchen (South Africa) 6-3, 6-2 to take the doubles crown.Title for Sasi New Delhi: GM Krishnan Sasikiran outsmarted world champion Rustam Kasimdzhanov of Uzbekistan to win the 8th Hogeschool Zeeland meet in Vlissingen. Sasikiran scored 7.5 points in nine rounds and romped thanks to a better tie-break score than the Dutch duo of Sergei Tiviakov and Daniel Stellwagen, according to information received here.  United lose London: Champions Arsenal began the defence of their Premier League title by outclassing Everton side 4-1 while Chelsea edged fellow title-contenders Manchester United 1-0 in two contrasting matches Sunday. Arsenal took the lead through Dennis Bergkamp on 23 minutes. Jose Antonio Reyes (39th), Frederik Ljungberg (54th) and substitute Robert Pires (83rd) got the Gunners other goals. Chelsea beat Manchester United via a 15th-minute Eidur Gudjohnsen goal. 
